  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nA couple months ago, the Activity Center app db state was designed to support a different set of features/expectations. Things changed and the AC is now relatively stable in some areas.\r\n\r\nThe current app db for the AC is more or less like this (I omited some keys):\r\n\r\n```clojure\r\n{:activity-center\r\n {:filter        {:status :unread\r\n                  :type   types/contact-request}\r\n  :notifications {types/no-type\r\n                  {:all    {:cursor   \"\"\r\n                            :loading? true\r\n                            :data     [...]}\r\n                   :unread {:cursor   \"\"\r\n                            :loading? false\r\n                            :data     [...]}}\r\n\r\n                  types/contact-request\r\n                  {:all    {:cursor   \"\"\r\n                            :loading? false\r\n                            :data     [...]}\r\n                   :unread {:cursor \"\"\r\n                            :data   [...]}}\r\n\r\n                  types/mention\r\n                  {:all    {:cursor   \"\"\r\n                            :loading? false\r\n                            :data     [...]}\r\n                   :unread {:cursor   \"\"\r\n                            :loading? false\r\n                            :data     [...]}}\r\n\r\n                  ;; and so on for other types (AC tabs in the UI)\r\n                  }}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs you can see, the UI is tracking the state of every AC tab, along with its loading state and cursor. This means that whenever notifications need to be *reconciled*, **complex logic needs to take place to correctly update the app db**. Over the last couple months this proved to be too complicated and bug-driven, requiring complicated test cases.\r\n\r\nOn top of that, **it's hard to make the reconciliation performant** without resorting to complementary indexes, otherwise full linear scans need to be performed in lots of collections.\r\n\r\nThe existing solution also duplicates a lot of notifications (the data is not normalized) and **more memory is consumed**.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nWe can remove a lot of the complexity if we assume that only the **current tab state** need to be kept in memory. When switching tabs, we always re-fetch the data. Given the communication between the backend and frontend is local and rather fast, this gives a good UX.\r\n\r\nProposal:\r\n\r\n```clojure\r\n{:activity-center\r\n {:filter        {:status :unread\r\n                  :type   types/contact-request}\r\n  :cursor        \"...\"\r\n  :loading?      true\r\n  :notifications [...]}}\r\n```\r\n",
